transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hey, my name is Terry Boat, I have a current prescription with you, and I would like to cancel please.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, give me one moment, let me fill up your account sir, one second.

Speaker 1: You did say Terry, correct?

Speaker 2: Terry Boat, V-O-G-T, mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Okie-dokie, alrighty sir, and I do see you are VIP with us here, do you mind if I ask why you're canceling the Viagra?

Speaker 2: Because I have enough Viagra to last me the next hundred years of my life.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I do see you got a few orders.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't get laid that much.

Speaker 1: Oh yeah, no, we totally understand, I mean, you don't have to get it this fast, you know, it could be a lot for anybody.

Speaker 2: No, we can always just stop sending it to you and give you some time, maybe like even six months where you're not being billed or shipped any and you can kind of order as needed going forward if you like.

Speaker 1: Well, I can always come back, right?

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, once your prescription's gone though, there won't be any refills to come back to.

Speaker 1: Right, nah, I'm good, just go ahead and cancel it please.

Speaker 2: Alrighty, I'll cancel.

Speaker 1: Alright, thank you.
